# Theme System — Mobile Styling Standards

## Rule: No Hardcoded Hex Colors

**NEVER** use hardcoded hex values in component code. ALL colors must come from `constants/theme.ts`.

❌ **FORBIDDEN:**

```typescript
backgroundColor: '#FFFFFF'
color: '#4F46E5'
<ActivityIndicator color="#4F46E5" />
placeholderTextColor="#A1A1AA"
```

✅ **REQUIRED:**

```typescript
import { colors, theme, gradients } from '../../constants/theme';

backgroundColor: colors.white
color: colors.primary[600]
<ActivityIndicator color={isDark ? colors.purple[500] : colors.primary[600]} />
placeholderTextColor={isDark ? colors.zinc[400] : colors.zinc[500]}
```

## Color Categories

| Category | Usage |
|----------|-------|
| `colors.primary[*]` | Brand (Indigo) |
| `colors.purple[*]` | Accent |
| `colors.zinc[*]` | Neutral / gray scale |
| `colors.success.*` | Success states (DEFAULT, light, dark, bg.light, bg.dark) |
| `colors.error.*` | Error states |
| `colors.warning.*` | Warning states |
| `gradients.light/dark.[feature]` | Screen header gradients |

## Theme-Aware Colors

```typescript
const isDark = currentTheme === 'dark';
const bgColor = theme[currentTheme].background.primary;
const textColor = theme[currentTheme].text.primary;
const borderColor = theme[currentTheme].border.light;
```

## Gradients

```typescript
<LinearGradient colors={isDark ? gradients.dark.feature : gradients.light.feature}>
  {children}
</LinearGradient>
```

## Styles Location

Keep styles in a dedicated `styles.ts` file per screen/component using `StyleSheet.create`. Never use inline style objects in JSX.

The only file permitted to contain hex color values is `constants/theme.ts`.
